  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2017-04-05T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Protecting Americans from Credit Entanglements Act of 2017 or the PACE Act of 2017\n\nThis bill amends the Truth in Lending Act to extend that Act's requirements to real property retrofit loans. A \"real property retrofit loan\" is a loan that is: (1) secured by an interest in real property; (2) repayable in installment payments made concurrently with the payment of property taxes on the real property; and (3) used to finance real property retrofits, including energy-efficiency upgrades, renewable-energy installations, seismic retrofits, water-conservation upgrades, and other similar improvements.\n\nBefore extending\u00a0a real property retrofit loan, the creditor must disclose that the loan will result in a lien on the real property securing the loan."
  }, 
